                                                <handDesc>
                                                    <summary>Horizontally extended script, with both angular and more round features (cf. Early Abbasid/Kufic); Qāf is sometimes marked with a dot below the consonantal skeleton; the dots on shīn are arranged either horizontally or in a triangle.</summary>
                                                    <handNote medium="brown" xml:id="hand-1">
                                                        <note xml:lang="en">Dark and light brown ink, with encircled dots dividing text units and some diacritics in red.</note>
                                                    </handNote>
                                                </handDesc>
                                                <bindingDesc>
